<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,364,293,319]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Oedaleus decorus</emphasis>
(Germar, 
<number box="[495,555,293,319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1826.0">1826</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,364,640]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">
A durable population, indicated by the collection of a series of specimens, has been recorded only at localities near Bzenec (Rezek 
<number box="[329,386,399,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1944.0">1944</number>
) in the period from the 
<number box="[660,718,399,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1940.0">1940</number>
s until the 
<number box="[837,895,399,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1960.0">1960</number>
s (Holuša 
<number box="[1010,1071,399,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="2012.0">2012</number>
). The last observations are from the 
<number box="[194,255,436,460]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1970.0">1970</number>
s. Given the intensive yearly surveys on sands around Bzenec during last 
<number box="[1095,1123,436,460]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="20.0">20</number>
years, this species must be considered regionally extinct (Holuša 
<number box="[579,640,471,495]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="2012.0">2012</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,364,640]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">
The area of sandy and shallow-soil grasslands is very limited and isolated in the territory of the CR (Chytrý et al. 
<number box="[185,244,543,567]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="2010.0">2010</number>
; AOPK 
<number box="[339,398,543,567]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="2011.0">2011</number>
), and therefore migration by flight from the areas of regular occurrence near Lake Balaton in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,250,581,605]" name="Hungary" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, which is about 
<quantity box="[432,517,580,604]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" unit="km" value="240.0">240 km</quantity>
distant, is unlikely, even though 
<taxonomicName box="[888,1011,580,604]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Oedaleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorus">
<emphasis box="[888,1011,580,604]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">
<collectingCountry box="[888,911,581,604]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">O</collectingCountry>
. decorus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered to be a species prone to mass migrations (Schmidt &amp; Lilge 
<number box="[545,605,615,639]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" value="1997.0">1997</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
